NOTE: Ubuntu/Lucid (10.4) contains Smuxi <u>0.7.1</u>, but it's
recommended to use <u>0.8</u> instead!

**Ubuntu/Lucid (10.04)** users can install Smuxi from this [PPA], just
run the following commands:

    sudo add-apt-repository ppa:meebey/ppa
    sudo aptitude update
    sudo aptitude install smuxi

Now you can start Smuxi from the GNOME or KDE menu.

  [PPA]: https://launchpad.net/~meebey/+archive/ppa
